<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="ios_baseiostate" id="ios_baseiostate">ios_base::iostate</a></h2>
<div class="level2">
<pre class="cpp code cpp"><span class="kw2">enum</span> iostate<span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
Specifies error state of a stream. It is bitmask type and has the following elements defined:

</p>
<div class="table sectionedit2"><table class="inline">
	<tr class="row0">
		<th class="col0"> Element </th><th class="col1"> Explanation </th>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row1">
		<td class="col0"> <code>badbit</code> </td><td class="col1"> indicates that irrecoverable stream error has occurred </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row2">
		<td class="col0"> <code>failbit</code> </td><td class="col1"> indicates that either input operation failed to read expected characters or output operation failed to generate the desired characters </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row3">
		<td class="col0"> <code>eofbir</code> </td><td class="col1"> indicates that associated input sequence has reached end-of-file </td>
	</tr>
</table></div>
